\subsection{Concept Recognition}\label{apdx:cpt_rec}

%We first recognize a set of source concepts $C_\mathbf{x}$ from the input sequence $\mathbf{x}$ by matching the text spans with their related concepts in $\mathcal{V}$. 
To recognize concepts from the input text sequence, we performed fuzzy matching with the lemmatized form of the surface texts using Spacy\footnote{https://spacy.io/} and filter out stop words . Following \citet{Guan2019StoryEG}, we only considered verbs and nouns as our candidate concepts to avoid ambiguous linking. We also conducted experiment without such a constraint but found the extracted graph is much noisier.

\subsection{Statistics of the Subgraphs}\label{apdx:subgraph}
The statistics of the extracted subgraphs on three datasets in shown in Table \ref{tab:subgraph-stats}. 
